				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Twist and shout<a name="12789"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 4 03 7:47 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I usually twist 4 songs, but to be honest, with missed notes and poor timing, I would guess I have 4 songs up a little over half the time.  3 songs is pretty much the standard I go for when I am with the main tank group or in a situation where a certain song is NEEDED to be up at all times (resists, ds, haste type stuff).  
<br />

<br />
Dont be to concerned with being a 3 song bard. 4 song bards are generally 3 song bards half the time anyway.
<br />

<br />
But twisting 4 is just like twisting 3.  Watch the cast bar, tap your hotkey as soon as the cast bar is done.  You should be able to keep 4 up with no missed notes, with a couple second overlap that allows you to make little timing errors</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><A HREF="http://www.bonsaikitten.com/">
