				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Twist and shout<a name="12793"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 4 03 9:34 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>In my experience, a whole lot depends on your computer system and likely your connection, as well.  I am a 3 song twister if I want to keep them all up all the time. I can do 4 if I don't mind losing one or both of the first two songs for a second or four.  I've got an old computer though it works fine for EQ.  I just can't twist 4 songs.  On my 2 box, which is significantly older and barely meets (not all) of EQ minimums, I can only twist 2 songs 90% of the time, so I don't play Sinfoninan on it.
<br />

<br />
Yes, there are things you can do to become a 4 twist bard that have to do with your hotkeys (not fancy) and your timing of recasts, but I've been semi-frustrated for a long time not being able to do it when it makes logical sence I could.
<br />

<br />
GL
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian</span></td>
