			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Twist and shout<a name="12803"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 4 03 2:57 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>one little bit of info i picked up a while back that helps with maintaining a 4 song twist (barring missed notes) is you do not have to wait until the song is 100% finished to start the next one.
<br />

<br />
i use the macro:
<br />
/stopsong
<br />
/cast 1-8 
<br />

<br />
as my hotkeys this will also help.
<br />

<br />
if the - represent the bar at say 5% ea -, then you want to see this:
<br />

<br />
-------------------
<br />

<br />
that is the start.  when the bar gets down to:
<br />
-
<br />

<br />
that is when you hit the next hotkey.  the last 1/4 sec or so will not count against you.  if you can keep that up, then you can keep up 4 songs with a little work.  otherwise i just stick with 3.
<br />

<br />
3 is cake walk and should be for any bard post teens.  only time i stress over keeping up all 4 is when im doing both slow and CC work in LDoN as there is no chanter or sham to do the job properly.  then i will do my best to keep 4 songs up 90% of the time.  
<br />

<br />
if im not in a situation that demands 4 songs, ill just do 3 and rotate 1 song out for that effect.  like rotating in mana vs DS one round or something like that.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
