				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Twist and shout<a name="14222"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 2 04 9:55 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Analysis (based on over 4 years barding and from reading other posts here and at the concert hall)
<br />

<br />
6 song twist - I messed around a long time ago with a BoH and had 6 icons up for a few seconds (no Amp).  There is no way mathematically possible to get 6 songs up without one song being long duration (amp) or insta click (BoH).
<br />

<br />
5 song twist - There is no way to keep 5 song icons up 100% of the time.  Song 1 will always drop 1 or 2 seconds after song 5 comes up.  You might get it going in a second again, but it isnt possible to have 5 up at all times, there WILL be 4 at least 1/3 of the time, and that is assuming there are no missed notes (and we know that is a big assumption).  
<br />
So with missed notes taken into acount, I would estimate (guess) that about 1/3 of the time 5 song icons would be up.  Not too shabby at all, and it is effective.  
<br />
If you insist you can keep 5 songs in the song box at all times, then I challenge you.  I will make a toon on your server, group with me and have 5 song icons up with no break for 10 minutes.  No long duration or insta clicks, and procs are NOT songs (I dont care if it IS called song of the seas LOL).  If you can do it, I will add a line on my sig that reflects your superior bard skeelz.  If you cant, you add a line on yours that reflects your loss.
<br />

<br />
4 song twist -  good bard, good connection, can keep 4 songs up 80-90% of the time.  The only thing that stops all 4 being up that 10-20% is missed notes.
<br />

<br />
3 song twist - 100% of the time as long as you dont get like 5 missed notes in a row (it has happened)</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><A HREF="http://www.bonsaikitten.com/">
