			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Twist and shout<a name="14223"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 2 04 10:07 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>One of the key factors in how many songs you can twist is how's your lag.  The number you want to pay the most attention to is the far right number on your lag meter.  If this goes over 100 you'll only be able to maintain 3 songs as the communication between your machine and SoE is not steady enough to get everthing together in the time needed.
<br />

<br />
I went from having a DSL connection, where that number hardly went above 70, to a dialup connection that is almost constantly above 100.  On the DSL I could maintain 4 songs quite well, but on the dialup I can hold a steady 3 and a 4th song if I don't mind losing a song or two.
<br />

<br />
Another trick is to not use the casting bar as your timer.  This will lead to a lot of problems when you get any kind of procing weapong, your epic for instance.  Instead have a window where the song start and stop messages will go and watch for the text saying the song has started.  I typically have messages that don't pertain to me (i.e. others hits, others misses) turned off so I'm not bombarded by stuff I don't need to worry about that winds up scrolling my song start message off the screen.
<br />

<br />
Anyhow, in most groups 3 songs is perfectly fine so don't beat yourself up if you can't maintain 4 or more songs.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=641487">Muse Ellorra Dannen</a><br>
