				<td colspan="2"><span>/agree Sapper
<br />

<br />
Just to comment on my post way up there... I got a new vid card for Christmas, sure that it would allow me to keep 4 songs up, because I was certain that computer power impacted the actual length of a 3-second cast with packets or whatever... FYI, my far right number has NEVER been below 100, it's normally in the 300-400 range when I'm not in battle or something important like that...
<br />

<br />
Moral of the story, I can sort-of keep 4 songs up, but invariably one will drop halfway into the recast time.  Not bad, but my worst culpret is me sitting there thunderstruck that I have 4 songs in my window! <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-13.gif" border="0" alt="LOL" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
That's using all 3 tick songs, though I do have better luck with the 21 second Warsong of Vah Shir than I do the 3 tick Rizonas Call of Flame.  Boy do groups love that song!  15% bonus to DD damage AND 30% overhaste! WOW, so glad I got that one from my spectral turn-in. Now if only I could get Requim of Time...
<br />

<br />
Anyway, I normally try NOT to do a 4 song twist these days. It seems I have grouped a lot with folks where either I was the only haste in a melee heavy group or my Zek was better.  I felt bad having haste/overhaste drop (hehe unless the MA happened to be casting at the time, ROFL).  So what I have taken to doing is to stagger my casts throughout a fight.  The first twist is Haste, overhaste, DS (PoV). Second (about halfway through the battle in LDoN) Is Haste, overhaste, mana, and the third is likely overhaste (if we have a haster) and mana.  About that time I'm turning off attack and jetting off to go grab another at 30% or so.  It takes a while to lull a room for a single pull.
<br />

<br />
Hope that helps,
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian</span></td>
