				<td colspan="2"><span>connection and good machines make it easier yes but its not mandatory I've been playing a Bard on the same machine for 4 years, granted I have a new one on order due here soon but in the mean time..on a 486 with a 64 graphic card I steadily twist 4 at all raids events and throw in a 5th occasionally. 
<br />
4 songs is standard if you include amplify, 5-6 songs are possible if your minimizing the lag interferance. Rarely is there a reason for you to have that many songs going though, bard friend of mine and myself had  2 bard ldon group going where we popped up 11 song effects at the same time, it was neat but not very useful really kept us too distracted twisting to be actually fulfilling the roles we needed. 
<br />
Don't let anyone convince you that its your gear or machines that make the bard. I've seen 65 bards on hummmmin machines that suck a$ at everything but kiting.. ooo impressive. 
<br />
I too love this site and have used it for ages directing new bards here when they have questions ect, Imho there is more to being a bard than how many icons you can get blinking.</span></td>
