				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Twist and shout<a name="14833"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 9 04 2:43 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I live in the US and play on a European server (Kane Bayle). I have cable connection but because of the distance to the server, lag can be very spiky at times. 
<br />
Solo, in a zone by myself (yes on Kane Bayle, there are lots of times I am the only one in the zone) I can keep 4 songs up about 70% of the time. In a group or busy zone, I can only keep 4 up about 20% of the time. The timing just isn't there. So normally I will do 3 songs and add another in once in awhile when I have nice string of no missed notes or stuns. I have never seen a situation where my group lost someone because I didn't have 4 songs up. Maybe that will change with higher levels/more songs to choose from, but right now 3 is fine. 
<br />
When I first started, there were lots of bards bragging about keeping 5-6 songs up, but I couldn't even keep 2 up reliably. I had never heard of songs that lasted longer than 3 ticks so I thought I was horrible. But I never got any complaints in groups so I kept practicing and researching and found that real bards only did 3-4 songs consistantly. I did a lot of experimenting with keyboard mapping and finally found a layout that I feel very comfortable with. 
<br />
If all you can do is 3 songs, then you are doing fine and should never get any complaints. If you do, then find another group.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
